Transformed space use for work, leisure, 
administration and services becomes the 
norm, increasing the intensity of home 
space use (9% utilization rate, that is, 
m2.degree-days), with moderate (2%) 
increase of non-residential space, mainly 
driven by population increase, as space 
use intensity is unchanged.
Return to pre-pandemic production structures 
and levels, with minor material reduction and 
intensity improvement (for example, as a legacy 
of cost pressures, staff shortage, automatization 
and so on). Overall, the change is small and only 
1% lower than it would be without a pandemic, 
yet 7% compared with 2019, with large regional 
